Language name: Diyari
Language number: 8367
Alternate names: 
Classification: Australian, Pama-Nyungan
Comments: Austin (1981) analyzes the alveolar trill /r/ as 
a stop /d/.  This phoneme does not occur initially; 
intervocalically it is a trill; in post-nasal and 
post-lateral position it is a voiced stop with trilled 
release [dr].  This stop is considered epenthetic here.

Sources: 

Austin, P.A. 1981. A Grammar of Diyari, South Australia. 
Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, New York.